%20the%20pitch%20deck%20that%20Pacaso%2C%20a%20luxury%20vacation%20home%20startup%2C%20used%20to%20crowdfund%20%2472%20million%20from%2017%2C500%20investors%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223551%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Pacaso%20was%20founded%20by%20Zillow%20co-founder%20CEO%20Spencer%20Rascoff%20and%20Austin%20Allison%2C%20former%20CEO%20of%20dotloop%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68fd3fbe0be9845f2dc51b78%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222663%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPacaso%20was%20founded%20by%20Zillow%20co-founder%20CEO%20Spencer%20Rascoff%20(left)%20and%20Austin%20Allison%2C%20former%20CEO%20of%20dotloop.%3Cp%3EPacaso%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPacaso%20raised%20%2472.5%20million%20via%20Reg%20A%2C%20a%20form%20of%20equity%20crowdfunding.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EReg%20A%20allows%20startups%20to%20raise%20up%20to%20%2475%20million%20from%20both%20accredited%20and%20non-accredited%20investors.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20'two%20birds%20with%20one%20stone'%20approach%2C%26quot%3B%20Pacaso's%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%2C%20Austin%20Allison%2C%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EHave%20you%20heard%20of%20Reg%20A%3F%20Neither%20had%20Austin%20Allison%20%E2%80%94%20until%20he%20used%20it%20to%20fund%20Pacaso%2C%20a%20real%20estate%20startup%20for%20luxury%20vacation%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllison%2C%20Pacaso's%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%2C%20started%20the%20company%20with%20Spencer%20Rascoff.%20They%20were%20both%20veterans%20of%20the%20real%20estate%20and%20consumer%20technology%20industries%20when%20they%20launched%20Pacaso%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPacaso%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsecond-home-startup-pacaso-is-fastest-ever-unicorn-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eplatform%20for%20fractional%20ownership%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20luxury%20vacation%20homes.%20The%20company%20facilitates%20the%20sale%20of%20properties%20in%20vacation%20destinations%20like%20Jackson%20Hole%2C%20Tuscany%2C%20and%20Napa%2C%20which%20are%20acquired%20through%20property-specific%20LLCs.%20Unlike%20timeshares%2C%20which%20allow%20multiple%20users%20the%20right%20to%20use%20a%20property%20for%20a%20set%20time%20each%20year%2C%20Pacaso%20allows%20clients%20to%20share%20equity%20in%20their%20properties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20reached%20a%20%241%20billion%20valuation%20just%20five%20months%20after%20launch%2C%20and%20at%20the%20time%2C%20it%20was%20the%20fastest%20startup%20in%20the%20US%20to%20hit%20unicorn%20status.%20Its%20current%20valuation%20is%20just%20short%20of%20%241%20billion%2C%20representatives%20for%20the%20company%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pair%20first%20funded%20Pacaso%20the%20traditional%20way%2C%20raising%20nearly%20%24220%20million%20over%20the%20course%20of%20four%20years%20from%20investors%20like%20SoftBank%2C%20Fifth%20Wall%2C%20Greycroft%2C%20and%20Maveron.%20By%202024%2C%20they%20began%20considering%20other%20options%20because%2C%20Allison%20said%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eventure%20capital%20suddenly%20felt%20limited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTraditional%20VC%20rounds%20put%20one%20or%20two%20investors%20on%20your%20cap%20table%2C%26quot%3B%20Allison%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20wanted%20more%20eyeballs%20on%20its%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20came%20across%20Reg%20A%2C%20a%20securities%20exemption%20that%20lets%20startups%20raise%20up%20to%20%2475%20million%20in%20a%2012-month%20period%20through%20a%20form%20of%20equity%20crowdfunding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20functions%20like%20a%20mini-IPO%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eallowing%20companies%20to%20raise%20money%20from%20both%20accredited%20and%20non-accredited%20investors%20%E2%80%94%20unlike%20Regulation%20D%2C%20which%20limits%20participation%20to%20accredited%20investors%20%E2%80%94%20while%20avoiding%20many%20of%20the%20regulatory%20hurdles%20associated%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-ipo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efull%20public%20offering%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllison%20said%20that%20Reg%20A%20presented%20%26quot%3Ba%20unique%20way%20to%20raise%20capital%20while%20simultaneously%20expanding%20brand%20awareness%20and%20customer%20acquisition.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20'two%20birds%20with%20one%20stone'%20approach%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPacaso's%20team%20spent%20about%20six%20months%20preparing%20before%20officially%20launching%20their%20Reg%20A%20campaign%2C%20which%20included%20making%20a%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Especialized%20pitch%20deck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpitch-deck-library%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estandard%20pitch%20deck%3C%2Fa%3E%20designed%20for%20investors%2C%20this%20needed%20to%20appeal%20to%20the%20masses.%20%26quot%3BWe%20wanted%20to%20make%20sure%20our%20deck%20was%20very%20compliant%2C%20very%20public-facing%2C%20and%20accurate%2C%26quot%3B%20Tom%20Mulholland%2C%20Pacaso's%20senior%20director%20of%20strategic%20initiatives%20and%20capital%20deployment%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20campaign%20was%20open%20between%20October%201%2C%202024%2C%20and%20September%2018%2C%202025.%20During%20that%20time%2C%20the%20company%20prepared%20four%20or%20five%20different%20versions%20of%20its%20deck.%20Mulholland%20said%20the%20team%20drafted%20it%20in%20large%20part%20from%20the%20top%20questions%20they%20received%20from%20potential%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20distributed%20the%20deck%20on%20its%20website.%20It%20also%20hosted%20investor%20webinars%20%E2%80%94%20which%20drew%20thousands%20of%20viewers%20over%20the%20course%20of%20the%20raise%20%E2%80%94%20where%20Pacaso's%20CEO%2C%20CFO%2C%20and%20president%20walked%20through%20the%20deck%20and%20answered%20questions%2C%20Mulholland%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20close%20of%20the%20campaign%2C%20Pacaso%20almost%20hit%20the%20%2475%20million%20cap%2C%20raising%20money%20from%2017%2C500%20investors.%20The%20minimum%20investment%20was%20just%20over%20%241%2C000.%20Allison%20said%20the%20average%20investment%20they%20received%20was%20a%20bit%20over%20%244%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20campaign%20drew%20a%20range%20of%20investors%2C%20but%20the%20typical%20demographic%20overlapped%20with%20the%20company's%20customer%20profile%20%E2%80%94%20high-net-worth%20individuals%20aged%2045%20and%20above%2C%20with%20household%20incomes%20of%20%24500%2C000%20or%20more%2C%20Allison%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnly%20a%20handful%20of%20companies%20have%20ever%20raised%20over%20%2470%20million%20through%20Reg%20A%20%E2%80%94%20we're%20among%20the%20top%20four.%20The%20average%20Reg%20A%20raise%20is%20closer%20to%20%2416%20million%2C%20so%20our%20campaign%20far%20exceeded%20expectations%2C%26quot%3B%20Allison%20said.%20%26quot%3BMany%20investors%20went%20on%20to%20become%20customers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESee%20Pacaso's%20pitch%20deck%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Pacaso%20pitch%20deck%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68fbeca5599d46a4ccc0d7d8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22405%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EPacaso%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Pacaso%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68fbed65c007ca8c2737a026%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22405%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EPacaso%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Pacaso%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68fbedae599d46a4ccc0d803%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D